rmont, a Catoctin Mountain Scenic Byway community. Location: Location: Thurmont, Maryland Status: Public domain. Tourism Council of Frederick County, Inc","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Downtown_Thurmont_-_NARA_-_7719782.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0d/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Marking_the_Brandy_Station_Battlefield_-_NARA_-_7719720.jpg/1280px-Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Marking_the_Brandy_Station_Battlefield_-_NARA_-_7719720.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0d/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Marking_the_Brandy_Station_Battlefield_-_NARA_-_7719720.jpg","cap":"Byway Marking the Brandy Station Battlefield","desc":"A historical marker adjacent to the byway marks the site of the Battle of Brandy Station; the site of the largest cavalry battle of the Civil War. Location: Location: Virginia (38.529° N 77.869° W) Status: Public domain. Photo courtesy of Lardner/Klein Landscape Architects, P.C.","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Marking_the_Brandy_Station_Battlefield_-_NARA_-_7719720.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9f/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Monocacy_Battlefield_-_NARA_-_7719775.jpg/1280px-Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Monocacy_Battlefield_-_NARA_-_7719775.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9f/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Monocacy_Battlefield_-_NARA_-_7719775.jpg","cap":"Byway Monocacy Battlefield","desc":"A beautiful sunny day among verdant fields belies the July 9, 1864 chaos of the Battle of Monocacy; the Civil War clash considered the battle that saved Washington D.C. Location: Location: Maryland Status: Public domain. Tourism Council of Frederick County, Inc","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Monocacy_Battlefield_-_NARA_-_7719775.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Monument_at_Gettysburg_National_Battlefield_Park_-_NARA_-_7719714.jpg/1280px-Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Monument_at_Gettysburg_National_Battlefield_Park_-_NARA_-_7719714.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/00/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Monument_at_Gettysburg_National_Battlefield_Park_-_NARA_-_7719714.jpg","cap":"Byway Monument at Gettysburg National Battlefield Park","desc":"South Mountain rises in the distance behind the Gettysburg Monument on the Gettysburg Battlefield , which contains broad fields where Union and Confederate troops clashed during one of the most critical turning points in the Civil War. Location: Location: Gettysburg, Pennsylvania (39.820° N 77.231° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of Gettysburg National Military Park","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Monument_at_Gettysburg_National_Battlefield_Park_-_NARA_-_7719714.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/58/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_National_Shrine_of_Our_Lady_Of_Lourdes_-_NARA_-_7719748.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/58/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_National_Shrine_of_Our_Lady_Of_Lourdes_-_NARA_-_7719748.jpg","cap":"Byway National Shrine of Our Lady Of Lourdes","desc":"One of the oldest replicas of the french monument, the Our Lady of Lourdes shrine towers above trees and gravestones. Location: Location: National Shrine of Our Lady Of Lourdes, Maryland Status: Public domain. Photo by S. Clyde","credit":"S. Clyde · Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_National_Shrine_of_Our_Lady_Of_Lourdes_-_NARA_-_7719748.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7c/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_National_Shrine_of_Our_Lady_of_Lourdes_-_NARA_-_7719786.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7c/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_National_Shrine_of_Our_Lady_of_Lourdes_-_NARA_-_7719786.jpg","cap":"Byway National Shrine of Our Lady of Lourdes","desc":"Above the lovely valley of Emmitsburg, situated high on the mountainside where nature displays itself in all its wild and picturesque glory, sits the National Shrine Grotto of Lourdes, which traces its lineage to the very beginnings of the spread of Catholicism in America. Location: Location: Maryland Status: Public domain. Photo by Lardner/Klein, Landscape Architects, P.C.","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_National_Shrine_of_Our_Lady_of_Lourdes_-_NARA_-_7719786.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/90/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Our_Lady_of_Lourdes_Grotto_-_NARA_-_7719757.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/90/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Our_Lady_of_Lourdes_Grotto_-_NARA_-_7719757.jpg","cap":"Byway Our Lady of Lourdes Grotto","desc":"Visitors examine the various trappings of worship in the Our Lady of Lourdes Grotto. Location: Location: Maryland Status: Public domain. Photo by A. E. Crane","credit":"A. E. Crane, U.S. Department of Transportation · Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Our_Lady_of_Lourdes_Grotto_-_NARA_-_7719757.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Our_Lady_of_Lourdes_National_Shrine_-_NARA_-_7719754.jpg/1280px-Journey_Through_Hallowed_Ground_Byway_-_Our_Lady_of_Lourdes_National_Shrine_-_NARA_-_7719754.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2d/